Tag.name: triggerTag
Tag.Property:
This tag shows value in database. If database value updated ten value tag automatically update.
value <-> triggerTag
triggerTag is the database field. value tag just a tag you can change in Ignition.
After creating an instance override the SQL Query propery of this tag with the specific query. For example, if a specific property of a quant output is required the serial may be "select setpointHighLimit from DtQuantOutputs where QuantOutputName = 'VCC205_TARGET'.
This tag has a tag change script that will update the value tag when this value changes from the database.

EventScripts.Event:
# Read qualified value for value tag val = system.tag.read("[.]value").value
# Check if value and trigger value the same if not update value if val != currentValue.value and val <> None: # currentValue is trigger tag system.tag.write("[.]value", currentValue.value)

Tag.name: updateSQL
Tag.Property: UPDATE DTQuantOutput SET SetpointHighLimit = ? WHERE QuantOutputName = 'VCT205X_TARGET'

Tag.name: value
Tag.Property:
This tag will automatically update the database value when you system.tag.write to this tag or manually cange in Designer. The tag will then update database field and is refleced in the triggeTag.
value <-> triggerTag
triggerTag is the database field. value tag just a tag you can change in Ignition.
This tag has a tag change script that will update the database based upon the insertSQL tags SQL call when the value changes.

EventScripts.Event:
# Read qualified value for trigger tag path valTrigger = system.tag.read("[.]triggerTag").value
# Check if value and trigger value the same if not update value if valTrigger != currentValue.value and valTrigger <> None: # currentValue is value tag #Update the database #Read insert SQL SQL = system.tag.read("[.]updateSQL").value system.db.runPrepUpdate(SQL, [currentValue.value])
